SIMPLE: buccan
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Buccan
<hw>Buc"can</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>boucan</ets>.
See <er>Buccaneer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wooden frame or grid
for roasting, smoking, or drying meat over fire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place where meat is smoked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Buccaned meat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buccan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Buccan
<hw>Buc"can</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>boucaner</ets>. See
<er>Buccaneer</er>.]</ety> <def>To expose (meat) in strips to fire and
smoke upon a buccan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Buccaneer</ent>⟦br⟧
